LINGFIELD PARK tracked the pace on the inside behind the duo vying for the lead and came three wide into the dfive, then shifted back to the inside and weakened. TRIBAL NOTION five wide into the first turn, stalked the pace on the outside four wide, weakened in the drive. COPPERHEAD CREEK was four wide on both turns, rated three wide and had no rally.
